To combine the three fractions, write them over the common denominator \((v-1)(v+1)\):

\[
\frac{v}{v+1}
+\frac{3}{v-1}
-\frac{6}{v^2-1}
=\frac{v(v-1)}{(v-1)(v+1)}
+\frac{3(v+1)}{(v-1)(v+1)}
-\frac{6}{(v-1)(v+1)}.
\]

Now add the numerators:

\[
v(v-1)+3(v+1)-6
= v^2 - v + 3v + 3 - 6
= v^2 +2v -3
= (v+3)(v-1).
\]

So the combined fraction is

\[
\frac{(v+3)(v-1)}{(v-1)(v+1)}
\;=\;
\frac{v+3}{\,v+1\,},
\]

with the understanding that \(v\neq\pm1\).
